api.github.com/repos/libgdx/libgdx/issues/6552","id":853983085,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDg1Mzk4MzA4NQ==","user":{"login":"NathanSweet","id":434010,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQzNDAxMA==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/434010?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet","html_url":"https://github.com/NathanSweet","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2021-06-03T16:00:28Z","updated_at":"2021-06-03T16:00:28Z","body":"```\r\nfloat glyphWidth = (glyph.width + glyph.xoffset) * fontData.scaleX - fontData.padRight;\r\n```\r\nThis code is taking the glyph width and x drawing offset to find the right edge of the glyph. It scales that and then subtracts any padding on the right edge. The idea is to find the exact right edge of the glyph based on the glyph texture region.\r\n\r\n```\r\nfloat glyphWidth = xAdvances[i-1];\r\n```\r\nThis code uses the x-advance, but that's not the same as the right edge of the glyph texture region. It may be too much (causing the bounds to not fit tightly around the text) or too little (causing the text to exceed the bounds).\r\n\r\nI'll try to investigate the problem soon. It's strange that it wraps when the text can easily fit. If you guys want to keep looking at it, the place to look is why the code doesn't go through the `// Glyph fits.` block.","author_association":"MEMBER","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/libgdx/libgdx/issues/comments/853983085/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"NathanSweet","id":434010,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQzNDAxMA==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/434010?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet","html_url":"https://github.com/NathanSweet","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/libgdx/libgdx/issues/comments/854057630","html_url":"https://github.com/libgdx/libgdx/issues/6552#issuecomment-854057630","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/libgdx/libgdx/issues/6552","id":854057630,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDg1NDA1NzYzMA==","user":{"login":"NathanSweet","id":434010,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQzNDAxMA==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/434010?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet","html_url":"https://github.com/NathanSweet","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2021-06-03T17:41:27Z","updated_at":"2021-06-03T17:41:27Z","body":"```\r\nif (x + glyphWidth - epsilon <= targetWidth) {\r\n```\r\nIn that code, the `x + glyphWidth` is `403.40753` and `targetWidth` is `403.40738`. The `epsilon` is `0.0001f` so not enough to allow evaluation to true. `0.001f` is enough, though it'd be nice to find a better way.\r\n\r\nThe label calculates the text width so it can align the wrapped text within the label. It then uses that width to layout the aligned text. A lot of problems are caused by the second layout using the exact width from the first layout. Some of those problems are legit bugs and it has been good to fix them. Some problems have been float rounding though.","author_association":"MEMBER","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/libgdx/libgdx/issues/comments/854057630/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"NathanSweet","id":434010,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQzNDAxMA==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/434010?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet","html_url":"https://github.com/NathanSweet","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Nath